Reasoning: The paper deals with the representation and equivalence of ordered and unordered trees, which are fundamental data structures in computer science. The use of SLT grammars and the concept of compressed tree canonization suggest that the paper belongs to the categories of data structures (cs.DS) and computational geometry (cs.CG). The mention of bisimulation equivalence and complexity bounds suggest that the paper may also belong to the categories of logic in computer science (cs.LO), computational complexity (cs.CC), and formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL).
